      "title": "[DC] moyashi0672@🔸guides: __**Disclaimer : This guide is susceptible of changes due to patch notes reworks",
      "summary": "__**Disclaimer : This guide is susceptible of changes due to patch notes reworks of interactions.**__\n\nTraphase is a online RNG PVP turn based gamemode with a MTG like gameplay style.\n\n__**General Tips**__\n\nIn Traphase there are 5 types of classes, Guardian ( Blue ), Warborn ( Red ), Luminis ( Purple ), Malphas ( Yellow ), Divinia ( Green ).\nBut for simplicity we will refer them by their colors.\n\n- NEVER THINK OF EACH CLASSES AS A DEFINITE TYPE OF CLASS, for example Blue type units who are supposed to be tank can also become DPS depending on the wheel equipped on, Green type units who are supposed to be healer can also become DPS, Red type units can sometimes also become healers and so does yellow.\n\nThey can be close to some kind of classes but not define into them.\n\n- READ THE KITS OF THE UNITS!!!\n\n- At low elo on both gamemode you won't lose many points if you lose the matches and you will most likely face against bots so it's better to enjoy limit testing there until you're ready to try and climb ( beginner protection up to 1500 elo ).\n\n- Precise Match button = the matchmaking will take longer but you won't have to deal with matchmakings like 5k elo vs 100 elo. It's more targeted to your elo range.\n\n- Simulated Rival button = you will be more likely to face against bots and after 180 sec of matchmaking it will be a forced match against a bot.\n\n- Each units have the same HP pool and damages as the opposing side and is not affected by dupes ( for example Leigh have base 70 max HP, if your opponent have a +12 leigh in their rooster, their leigh will still remain at 70 max HP ).",
